WEBVTT

00:04.265 --> 00:06.136
-COME ON IN, I'LL BUY
YA A GLASS OF WINE.

00:06.267 --> 00:07.442
-THAT SOUNDS GOOD.

00:08.486 --> 00:11.011
DINNER WAS WONDERFUL, MITCH.

00:11.141 --> 00:12.577
-AW, THANK YOU. IT'S MY
FAVORITE RESTAURANT.

00:12.708 --> 00:13.448
I KNEW YOU'D LIKE IT.

00:13.578 --> 00:14.449
-HOBIE: DAD?

00:14.971 --> 00:15.841
-HOBIE?

00:16.712 --> 00:18.061
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'
HOME, I THOUGHT

00:18.192 --> 00:19.149
YOU WENT TO THE RIVER?

00:19.280 --> 00:20.629
-YEAH PLANS FELL THROUGH.

00:20.759 --> 00:21.630
-OH.

00:22.979 --> 00:25.851
CARRIE, THIS IS
MY SON, HOBIE.

00:25.982 --> 00:27.549
-HI, HOBIE.
-HOBIE: HI.

00:27.679 --> 00:29.812
I THOUGHT YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO GO TO SAN DIEGO?

00:29.942 --> 00:31.640
-PLANS FELL THROUGH.

00:32.293 --> 00:33.598
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ANYWAY?

00:33.729 --> 00:34.730
-UM...

00:36.079 --> 00:37.602
-KATE: HI, MR. BUCHANNON.

00:37.733 --> 00:40.170
-HOBIE: DAD, CARRIE,
THIS IS KATE.

00:40.866 --> 00:41.650
I WAS...

00:41.780 --> 00:43.130
-WE WERE...

00:43.260 --> 00:44.174
-RESTING.

00:45.001 --> 00:46.220
-RESTING?

00:46.350 --> 00:48.526
WELL YOU LOOK
A LITTLE TIRED.

00:48.657 --> 00:50.789
EXCUSE ME A MINUTE, COULD
I TALK TO YOU FOR A SECOND?

00:51.529 --> 00:52.530
EXCUSE ME.

00:56.012 --> 00:57.535
THIS IS A LITTLE AWKWARD.

00:57.666 --> 00:59.320
-YEAH.

00:59.450 --> 01:00.756
WHY DON'T YOU GUYS GO OUT
FOR THAT GLASS OF WINE?

01:00.886 --> 01:01.931
-MITCH: I WAS
THINKING MORE ABOUT

01:02.062 --> 01:03.498
THE TWO OF YOU GOING OUT.

01:03.628 --> 01:05.021
-HOBIE: WHAT? I
WAS HERE FIRST.

01:05.152 --> 01:06.370
-YOU COULD HAVE
CALLED AND LET ME KNOW.

01:06.501 --> 01:07.719
-YOU COULD HAVE CALLED
ME, I'VE BEEN HERE!

01:07.850 --> 01:09.156
-ALRIGHT, LET'S
BE REASONABLE.

01:09.286 --> 01:10.853
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE
STAY HERE TOGETHER?

01:10.983 --> 01:13.116
-HOBIE: WHAT? I DON'T
WANNA DOUBLE WITH MY DAD.

01:13.247 --> 01:14.944
-ANY SUGGESTIONS?

01:15.640 --> 01:16.554
-YEAH, I'LL GO UP
TO MY ROOM.

01:16.685 --> 01:17.903
-NO WAY.

01:18.034 --> 01:19.688
-WHY NOT?

01:19.818 --> 01:21.255
-I'M RESPONSIBLE, YOU'RE NOT
TAKIN' A GIRL TO YOUR ROOM.

01:21.385 --> 01:22.604
-HOBIE: DAD, IT'S THE 90S!

01:22.734 --> 01:23.605
-I DON'T CARE IF
IT'S THE MILLENNIUM,

01:23.735 --> 01:24.606
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

01:24.736 --> 01:25.824
-FINE.

01:25.955 --> 01:26.608
YOU GO UP TO
YOUR ROOM THEN.

01:26.738 --> 01:27.609
-HOBIE!

01:27.739 --> 01:28.610
-I'M 18!

01:28.740 --> 01:29.611
-IT DOESN'T MATTER.

01:29.741 --> 01:31.047
YOU'RE UNDER MY ROOF.

01:31.178 --> 01:32.396
-IT'S MY ROOF TOO, RIGHT?

01:32.527 --> 01:33.789
-I BOUGHT THE HOUSE,
I PAY THE BILLS.

01:34.659 --> 01:35.486
-WHAT DOES THAT MAKE ME?

01:35.617 --> 01:36.748
A HOUSE GUEST?

01:36.879 --> 01:37.836
-BOTH: GOOD NIGHT!

01:37.967 --> 01:39.969
-KATE: THANKS, IT WAS GREAT.

01:40.578 --> 01:41.449
-UM...

01:48.456 --> 01:52.460
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

01:56.420 --> 01:59.206
-♪ SOME PEOPLE
STAND IN THE DARKNESS ♪

02:00.294 --> 02:03.819
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

02:03.949 --> 02:07.866
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

02:07.997 --> 02:11.000
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

02:11.740 --> 02:14.003
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

02:14.699 --> 02:16.701
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALRIGHT ♪

02:20.140 --> 02:25.145
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY I
WON'T LET YOU OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

02:28.887 --> 02:32.543
♪ I'LL BE READY
I'LL BE READY ♪

02:32.674 --> 02:34.763
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

02:34.893 --> 02:36.721
♪ NO DON'T YOU FEAR

02:36.852 --> 02:39.594
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:40.116 --> 02:45.121
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:59.353 --> 03:03.835
-[PEOPLE TALKING]

03:03.966 --> 03:04.793
-CHRIS: HERE
YOU GO, HOBE.

03:06.229 --> 03:07.622
-ALRIGHT. THANKS
FOR THE RIDE, CHRIS!

03:07.752 --> 03:09.101
HEY, TELL MY DAD
I'LL BE RIGHT UP.

03:09.232 --> 03:10.451
I GOTTA GO TO MY CAR.

03:15.456 --> 03:16.935
-MAN: HEY, MAN.
HOW YOU DOIN'?

03:24.247 --> 03:29.252
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

04:03.591 --> 04:04.418
-EXCUSE ME.

04:05.680 --> 04:06.463
IS THIS YOUR CAR?

04:06.594 --> 04:07.508
-OH YEAH, YOU KNOW.

04:08.073 --> 04:09.336
JUST LEFT THE KEYS IN IT.

04:09.466 --> 04:14.254
-[INTENSE MUSIC]

04:17.082 --> 04:19.346
-WOMAN: HEY, WHAT
ARE THESE GUYS DOING?

04:19.868 --> 04:21.303
-MAN: HEY, HEY!

04:22.523 --> 04:23.393
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

04:31.967 --> 04:32.837
-WHOA!

04:35.405 --> 04:36.319
-WOMAN: WHOA, DUDE!

04:53.771 --> 04:54.598
-YOU OKAY?

04:54.729 --> 04:56.296
-NO, MY JAW'S
KINDA SORE.

04:56.426 --> 04:57.775
-YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
GET SOME ICE ON THAT.

04:59.211 --> 05:00.082
LISTEN, I'M GONNA GO
CALL THE CENTER, ALRIGHT?

05:00.212 --> 05:00.996
I'LL SEE YA LATER.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.127
-ALRIGHT, THANKS AGAIN.

05:02.258 --> 05:03.128
-ALEX: ANYTIME!

05:09.134 --> 05:12.877
-[PEOPLE TALKING]

05:25.194 --> 05:25.977
-MITCH: HEY!

05:26.108 --> 05:27.327
-HEY.

05:27.457 --> 05:28.328
-WHAT'S UP?

05:30.025 --> 05:31.200
-WE GOTTA TALK.

05:31.722 --> 05:32.549
-ABOUT WHAT?

05:34.725 --> 05:35.552
-I'M MOVING OUT.

05:38.207 --> 05:39.600
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE MOVIN' OUT?

05:41.036 --> 05:42.342
-I WANT MY OWN PLACE.

05:43.995 --> 05:45.519
-HOBIE, IS THIS
ABOUT LAST NIGHT?

05:45.649 --> 05:47.042
-I'M NOT A LITTLE
KID ANYMORE.

05:48.173 --> 05:50.480
I GRADUATED HIGH SCHOOL,
I GOT MY OWN JOB--

05:50.611 --> 05:52.090
-LOOK, IF YOU'RE UPSET
ABOUT IT, IT'S MY HOUSE,

05:52.221 --> 05:53.831
I PAY THE BILLS,
I'M SORRY.

05:54.397 --> 05:55.790
KINDA REMINDED
ME OF MY OWN DAD.

05:57.269 --> 05:58.488
-I JUST NEED SPACE.

05:59.141 --> 06:00.577
-THERE'S PLENTY OF
SPACE FOR TWO OF US.

06:00.708 --> 06:01.883
-WELL, PRIVACY.

06:02.013 --> 06:04.538
ANYWAY, JB AND CONNER
HAVE THEIR OWN APARTMENT

06:05.060 --> 06:06.583
AND I'M MOVIN'
IN WITH 'EM.

06:06.714 --> 06:08.193
-NOW THAT'S TWO ROOMMATES,
THAT'S LESS PRIVACY.

06:08.324 --> 06:11.632
-YEAH BUT THEY'RE BUDDIES
THEY'RE NOT MY DAD.

06:12.284 --> 06:13.721
-WELL, WHAT IF I SAY NO?

06:13.851 --> 06:16.158
-I'M 18, LEGALLY
YOU CAN'T SAY NO.

06:17.725 --> 06:18.943
-WOW.

06:19.074 --> 06:20.336
IS THAT AN ULTIMATUM
OR A CHALLENGE?

06:20.467 --> 06:21.729
-WHY? YOU GONNA
SEND ME TO MY ROOM?

06:21.859 --> 06:23.470
-HEY, I DON'T LIKE
YOUR TONE HERE.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.254
-I DON'T LIKE BEING
TREATED LIKE A KID.

06:26.864 --> 06:27.735
-ALRIGHT.

06:28.257 --> 06:29.127
YOU'RE 18.

06:29.998 --> 06:31.303
BUT YOU'RE ONLY 18.

06:32.000 --> 06:33.784
YOU GOT RESPONSIBILITIES
TO THINK ABOUT,

06:33.915 --> 06:36.700
GAS, FOOD, RENT,
INSURANCE, A CAR.

06:36.831 --> 06:38.049
-YEAH, I KNOW.

06:39.442 --> 06:40.312
-YOU THINK YOU KNOW.

06:41.792 --> 06:42.619
-I'M LEAVING.

06:45.143 --> 06:46.318
-THAT'S A MISTAKE.

06:48.582 --> 06:49.626
-I DON'T THINK IT IS.

06:51.149 --> 06:52.542
I'LL BE BY TO PICK
MY STUFF UP TONIGHT.

06:53.891 --> 06:56.720
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:10.517 --> 07:11.300
-ALEX!

07:11.431 --> 07:12.214
-HEY, NEELY.

07:12.344 --> 07:13.563
-HEY.

07:13.694 --> 07:14.912
OKAY IF I TX
WITH CODY TOMORROW?

07:15.043 --> 07:16.348
ASHLEY'S GOT A
DOCTOR'S APPOINTMENT.

07:16.479 --> 07:17.262
-SHE ALRIGHT?

07:17.393 --> 07:18.307
-YEAH, SHE'S FINE.

07:18.438 --> 07:19.700
JUST A WELL BABY CHECKUP.

07:19.830 --> 07:20.788
-YOU CHECK IT OUT WITH CODY?

07:20.918 --> 07:21.789
-YEAH, IT'S FINE WITH HIM.

07:21.919 --> 07:22.877
SO?

07:23.007 --> 07:24.052
-YEAH, IT'S FINE WITH ME.

07:24.182 --> 07:25.053
-OH, THANKS.
-YEAH.

07:25.183 --> 07:26.576
-NEELY: BIG BIKE RIDE?

07:26.707 --> 07:28.839
-NO, I'M ACTUALLY JUST
HEADED UP PCH AWAYS.

07:28.970 --> 07:30.537
GOIN' TO MY GRANNY'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY.

07:30.667 --> 07:31.929
-OOH, HOW OLD IS SHE?

07:32.060 --> 07:33.844
-SHE'S 93 BELIEVE
IT OR NOT.

07:33.975 --> 07:34.802
-WHOA!

07:34.932 --> 07:36.630
-YEAH.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.240
WELL LISTEN, I GOTTA GET GOIN',
I GOTTA BE THERE BY SIX.

07:38.370 --> 07:40.198
-HMM, GRANDMA GOES
TO BED EARLY, HUH?

07:40.329 --> 07:43.114
-NO, SHE'S CATCHING A PLANE
TO VEGAS WITH HER BOYFRIEND.

07:43.245 --> 07:44.464
93!

07:45.029 --> 07:46.291
[ALEX LAUGHS]

07:51.688 --> 07:55.649
-[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING]

07:55.779 --> 07:59.914
-[INTENSE ROCK MUSIC]

08:44.567 --> 08:45.437
-GOD!

08:46.743 --> 08:47.614
JERK.

08:57.275 --> 08:58.450
-THIS ISN'T GONNA
WORK, JASON.

08:59.408 --> 09:00.322
I DON'T LIKE IT.

09:01.192 --> 09:02.063
-TOO LATE.

09:02.759 --> 09:03.760
-IF MARCUS FINDS OUT...

09:04.413 --> 09:05.283
-HE WON'T.

09:12.552 --> 09:14.292
BEN, THIS IS JASON.
DO YOU READ ME?

09:14.423 --> 09:15.946
-YEAH, GO AHEAD I READ YOU.

09:16.468 --> 09:18.296
-LISTEN, THERE'S BEEN A
CHANGE IN THE DROP ZONE.

09:18.427 --> 09:19.907
SANTA BARBARA'S TOO HOT.

09:20.037 --> 09:21.299
-I HEAR YA.

09:21.822 --> 09:23.780
-WE'LL MEET YOU JUST PAST
THE JETTY IN CARPINTERIA.

09:23.911 --> 09:24.738
-BEN: ALRIGHT.

09:31.048 --> 09:35.618
-[INTENSE ROCK MUSIC]

09:47.543 --> 09:48.457
-[TRUCK HORN BLARES]

09:53.288 --> 09:55.072
-[BEN SCREAMS]

10:22.665 --> 10:24.014
-WOMAN: WHAT THE
HELL IS GOING ON?

10:24.536 --> 10:25.668
-JASON: WE'D
BETTER FIND OUT.

10:30.325 --> 10:31.195
YOU OKAY, MAN?

10:32.327 --> 10:33.415
WHAT HAPPENED?

10:33.545 --> 10:34.590
-BEN: TRUCK RAN
ME OFF THE ROAD.

10:38.420 --> 10:39.421
[BEN COUGHS]

10:43.033 --> 10:44.295
-WHERE'S THE PACKAGE?

10:44.426 --> 10:45.819
-[BEN LAUGHS]

10:48.169 --> 10:49.431
-[GUNSHOT]

10:49.561 --> 10:50.562
-IT'S GOTTA BE
ON HIS MOTORCYCLE,

10:50.693 --> 10:52.260
GET US BACK OVER THERE.

10:53.130 --> 10:54.349
-WOMAN: WHY DID
YOU SHOOT HIM?

10:54.479 --> 10:55.567
-JASON: JUST DRIVE
THE DAMN BOAT!

11:02.792 --> 11:06.753
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

11:15.544 --> 11:17.024
-WOMAN: WHAT IF IT'S
NOT ON THE BIKE?

11:17.677 --> 11:18.852
-JASON: WHERE
ELSE COULD IT BE?

11:19.591 --> 11:20.854
-WOMAN: HOW'D THIS GET
SO MESSED UP?

11:20.984 --> 11:22.116
-JASON: JUST GET
IN THE WATER!

11:34.519 --> 11:39.568
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

12:03.070 --> 12:04.854
-STOP FIGHTING ME,
I'M A LIFEGUARD.

12:04.985 --> 12:05.986
COME ON, LET ME HELP YOU.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.553
-WE GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE!

12:09.641 --> 12:11.687
-IT LOOKS LIKE IT WENT
STRAIGHT THROUGH, THAT'S GOOD.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.254
WE'VE GOTTA
STOP THE BLEEDING.

12:14.429 --> 12:15.473
-THEY TRIED TO KILL ME.

12:15.604 --> 12:16.997
-WHO ARE THESE PEOPLE?

12:17.562 --> 12:22.437
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:41.717 --> 12:43.327
-THERE'S SOME UNDERWATER
CAVES IN THOSE CLIFFS,

12:43.458 --> 12:44.502
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

12:45.286 --> 12:46.069
-BEN: WHERE'S THE CAVE?

12:46.200 --> 12:47.375
-IT'S OVER HERE.

12:47.505 --> 12:48.637
THE TIDES COVERED IT UP.

12:49.420 --> 12:50.508
ALRIGHT, LISTEN.

12:51.161 --> 12:52.554
WE'RE GONNA GO
FOR A LITTLE SWIM.

12:53.163 --> 12:54.686
I WANT YOU TO TAKE A
DEEP BREATH, ALRIGHT?

12:55.426 --> 12:56.993
-I DON'T THINK I CAN.

12:57.951 --> 12:58.908
-WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

12:59.039 --> 13:00.605
-BEN.

13:00.736 --> 13:03.130
-BEN, I'M NOT ASKING
YOU, I'M TELLING YOU, OKAY?

13:04.522 --> 13:05.959
-I CAN'T, I CAN'T.

13:06.089 --> 13:07.438
-BEN, LISTEN TO ME!

13:08.004 --> 13:11.747
I AM MISSING MY GRANDMA'S 93RD
BIRTHDAY FOR THIS, ALRIGHT?

13:12.530 --> 13:13.314
-ALRIGHT.

13:13.444 --> 13:14.315
ALRIGHT.

13:29.069 --> 13:30.461
-COULDN'T BE DONE, HUH?

13:32.072 --> 13:33.377
-IS IT REALLY
WORTH ALL THIS?

13:33.508 --> 13:35.379
-THE LATEST DESIGNER DRUG.

13:36.337 --> 13:37.729
WHATEVER GETS YOU
THROUGH THE NIGHT.

13:38.643 --> 13:39.731
-WHAT IF THEY
FIND THE BODY?

13:40.471 --> 13:41.472
-THEY WON'T.

13:41.603 --> 13:42.822
HE'S SHARK BAIT.

13:48.044 --> 13:49.350
-WOMAN: DAMN!

13:49.480 --> 13:50.307
-WHERE THE HELL
DID SHE COME FROM?

13:56.313 --> 13:58.750
-WOMAN: JASON, LET'S RUN
WHILE WE GOT A CHANCE,

13:58.881 --> 14:00.448
WE GOT THE STUFF.

14:00.578 --> 14:02.580
-NO, WE GOTTA KILL HIM
BEFORE HE TALKS TO MARCUS!

14:02.711 --> 14:04.017
THEN HE RIPPED HIM OFF!

14:04.147 --> 14:06.062
OTHERWISE WE'RE DEAD, BABY.

14:07.194 --> 14:08.848
-[GUNSHOTS]

14:16.638 --> 14:18.640
-WE'RE GOIN' UNDER,
TAKE A DEEP BREATH!

14:21.251 --> 14:22.426
-[GUNSHOTS]

14:35.918 --> 14:36.876
-WHERE'D THEY GO?

14:38.094 --> 14:39.879
-JASON: THEY GOTTA BE HERE
SOMEWHERE, KEEP LOOKIN'.

14:45.536 --> 14:47.234
-GOOD JOB, BEN.

14:47.364 --> 14:49.714
MAYBE MY GRANNY'LL SAVE US
A PIECE OF BIRTHDAY CAKE.

14:54.110 --> 14:55.329
WE SHOULD BE OKAY IN HERE,

14:55.459 --> 14:57.244
TIL THE TIDE FILLS
UP THE CAVE.

14:59.594 --> 15:02.162
PLEASE TELL ME THIS
IS NOT ABOUT DRUGS.

15:02.292 --> 15:03.293
-NOPE.

15:03.424 --> 15:04.599
DIAMONDS.

15:04.729 --> 15:07.907
I'M A LOW-PROFILE COURIER.

15:08.777 --> 15:10.344
-OBVIOUSLY NOT LOW ENOUGH.

15:14.522 --> 15:19.222
-[RELAXING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]

15:25.794 --> 15:26.708
-HOW YOU BEEN STRANGER?

15:26.838 --> 15:28.014
-ALRIGHT I GUESS.

15:28.144 --> 15:29.711
-WELL YOU KNOW,
I MISS YOU, HOBIE.

15:29.841 --> 15:30.625
-YEAH--

15:30.755 --> 15:31.582
-SO DOES ASHLEY.

15:31.713 --> 15:32.844
-I MISS YOU GUYS TOO.

15:33.454 --> 15:35.673
-LISTEN, I HOPE WHAT HAPPENED
BETWEEN YOUR DAD AND ME

15:35.804 --> 15:37.327
DOESN'T CHANGE THINGS
BETWEEN YOU AND ME.

15:37.458 --> 15:38.676
-OH, NO WAY.

15:39.286 --> 15:40.330
IS HE IN HEADQUARTERS
RIGHT NOW?

15:40.461 --> 15:41.288
-YEAH.

15:41.418 --> 15:42.376
THERE A PROBLEM?

15:42.942 --> 15:44.508
-WE'RE NOT
EXACTLY COOL LATELY.

15:44.639 --> 15:45.683
-OH, WHAT HAPPENED?

15:45.814 --> 15:46.946
-I MOVED OUT.

15:47.076 --> 15:48.382
-WOW, WE GOT A
LOT IN COMMON.

15:50.036 --> 15:51.602
-I JUST WANT MY
OWN PLACE, YOU KNOW?

15:51.733 --> 15:52.690
MY OWN LIFE?

15:52.821 --> 15:54.562
-OH, I CAN UNDERSTAND THAT.

15:55.084 --> 15:56.390
BUT I'M GUESSING
THAT MITCH DOESN'T.

15:56.520 --> 15:57.391
-NOPE.

15:58.261 --> 15:59.480
-WELL BEST OF LUCK TO YA.

16:00.176 --> 16:00.960
WHERE YA LIVIN'?

16:01.090 --> 16:02.526
-THAT'S MY PROBLEM.

16:02.657 --> 16:04.441
I WAS SUPPOSED TO MOVE
IN WITH A COUPLE BUDDIES

16:04.572 --> 16:05.921
AND NOW THE LANDLORD
WON'T LET MORE THAN

16:06.052 --> 16:07.053
TWO PEOPLE LIVE THERE.

16:07.183 --> 16:08.576
-OUCH.

16:08.706 --> 16:09.664
TOO MUCH PRIDE TO GO
HOME AND NOT ENOUGH

16:09.794 --> 16:10.970
MONEY TO STAY AWAY.

16:11.100 --> 16:12.362
-EXACTLY.

16:13.015 --> 16:14.451
I WAS KINDA HOPIN'
YOU'D HAVE SOME IDEAS.

16:14.582 --> 16:16.453
-[NEELY LAUGHS]

16:16.584 --> 16:17.411
YEAH I GOT A GOOD ONE.

16:17.541 --> 16:18.455
-OH REALLY?

16:19.195 --> 16:21.023
-NO. FORGET IT, IT WOULD
ONLY MAKE THINGS WORSE.

16:21.154 --> 16:22.459
-I KNOW, BUT WHAT?

16:22.590 --> 16:23.721
-YOUR DAD WOULD GO
BALLISTIC IF I GOT

16:23.852 --> 16:24.592
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THIS THING.

16:24.722 --> 16:26.159
-NEELY, I'M DYIN' HERE.

16:26.289 --> 16:27.421
WHAT DO YOU GOT FOR ME?

16:27.551 --> 16:29.162
-NO, NO, NO, NO.

16:32.034 --> 16:33.775
LISTEN.

16:33.905 --> 16:35.690
I GOT A REALLY BIG APARTMENT
AND A BEAUTIFUL LITTLE GIRL

16:35.820 --> 16:37.561
WHO NEEDS SOMEBODY TO
HELP ME TAKE CARE OF HER.

16:37.692 --> 16:39.128
WE COULD HELP
EACH OTHER OUT.

16:39.259 --> 16:40.303
-HOW?

16:40.434 --> 16:42.044
ME LIVE WITH
YOU AND ASHLEY?

16:42.175 --> 16:44.046
-YEAH, YEAH WE COULD
WORK OUT A SCHEDULE.

16:44.177 --> 16:46.483
YOU COULD WATCH ASHLEY IN
EXCHANGE FOR YOUR RENT.

16:46.614 --> 16:47.832
COME AND GO AS YOU PLEASE.

16:48.572 --> 16:49.530
-SO BE A NANNY.

16:49.660 --> 16:50.879
-OH IN YOUR CASE A MANNY.

16:51.010 --> 16:52.315
-[BOTH LAUGH]

16:53.099 --> 16:54.926
-NO, FORGET IT, YOU KNOW MITCH
WOULD ONLY HATE ME MORE.

17:01.585 --> 17:02.456
-ALRIGHT.

17:03.239 --> 17:04.414
THERE.

17:04.545 --> 17:06.068
KELP MAY NOT
SMELL SO GREAT BUT

17:06.199 --> 17:07.590
WHEN YOU NEED A
BLANKET, IT IS THE BEST

17:07.722 --> 17:09.244
THE OCEAN HAS TO OFFER.

17:10.986 --> 17:11.943
YOU GETTIN' WARMER?

17:12.553 --> 17:13.554
-OH YEAH.

17:13.684 --> 17:15.425
SWEATIN' BULLETS.

17:22.040 --> 17:22.998
-ALRIGHT.

17:23.520 --> 17:24.652
LISTEN, I'M GONNA BE
RIGHT BACK, OKAY?

17:24.781 --> 17:25.566
-WHOA, WHOA!

17:25.695 --> 17:27.262
WHERE YOU GOIN'?

17:27.394 --> 17:28.351
-I'M GONNA GO GET SOMETHIN'
TO STOP THIS BLEEDING.

17:30.005 --> 17:32.399
I WILL COME BACK.
I PROMISE, OKAY?

17:33.182 --> 17:34.618
-OKAY, OKAY.

17:34.749 --> 17:35.619
-ALRIGHT.

17:36.316 --> 17:37.143
OKAY.

17:44.454 --> 17:48.632
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

18:13.788 --> 18:14.745
-WOMAN: MAYBE THEY DROWNED.

18:15.529 --> 18:16.660
-UH-UH.

18:17.226 --> 18:18.880
WHOEVER THAT CHICK IS, SHE
KNOWS WHAT SHE'S DOING.

18:22.492 --> 18:23.624
HIGH TIDE'S
COMING IN SOON.

18:24.799 --> 18:25.756
THEY'LL HAVE TWO CHOICES.

18:26.409 --> 18:29.891
EITHER DROWN IN A
CAVE, OR COME OUT.

18:37.638 --> 18:38.508
-OKAY.

18:44.645 --> 18:45.602
GOOD.

18:46.212 --> 18:47.735
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE
GETTING SOME COLOR BACK.

18:47.865 --> 18:48.692
-YEAH?

18:48.823 --> 18:49.824
[BEN COUGHS]

18:50.738 --> 18:52.566
WELL, I'LL HAVE TO GET ONE
OF THESE FOR THE HOUSE.

18:52.696 --> 18:55.699
-ALRIGHT, OKAY.

18:55.830 --> 18:56.744
-WHAT'S THAT?

18:57.614 --> 18:58.528
-SEA GRASS.

18:58.659 --> 18:59.486
I'M GONNA MAKE A COMPRESS,

18:59.616 --> 19:00.835
IT'LL STOP THE BLEEDING.

19:00.965 --> 19:03.707
-WHERE'D YOU
LEARN ALL OF THIS?

19:03.838 --> 19:06.232
-OCEAN SURVIVAL
CLASS, I'M A LIFEGUARD.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.190
WE DIVE AROUND HERE
A LOT, THAT'S HOW

19:08.321 --> 19:09.322
I KNEW WHERE THE CAVE WAS.

19:10.671 --> 19:12.368
YOU KNOW, YOUR FRIENDS ARE OUT
THERE WAITIN' FOR HIGH TIDE.

19:13.978 --> 19:14.979
-THEY WON'T GIVE UP.

19:16.546 --> 19:18.331
-GOT A QUESTION
FOR YA, BEN.

19:18.940 --> 19:21.160
YOU HEDGE HOP ME ON MY BIKE,
YOU DO A TWO AND A HALF

19:21.290 --> 19:24.119
GAINER INTO THE OCEAN,
YOU WANNA TELL ME WHY?

19:24.250 --> 19:26.295
-A TRUCK DROPPED A
CARGO ON THE ROAD.

19:26.904 --> 19:30.473
I TRIED TO DODGE IT BUT I
LOST CONTROL ON THE TURN.

19:31.039 --> 19:32.823
-ALEX: WHY ARE THESE
PEOPLE SO AGGRESSIVE?

19:33.607 --> 19:36.740
-THEY ARE BEING MY PACKAGE
IS WORTH TWO MILLION DOLLARS.

19:37.785 --> 19:39.178
-TWO MILLION DOLLAR DIAMOND?

19:39.700 --> 19:40.527
-BEN: YEP.

19:40.657 --> 19:41.702
-CAN I SEE IT?

19:41.832 --> 19:43.834
-WENT DOWN WITH MY BIKE.

19:43.965 --> 19:46.402
-UH-HUH, AND THEY
THINK YOU HAVE IT, RIGHT?

19:46.533 --> 19:47.360
-BEN: YEP.

19:48.665 --> 19:50.406
-TWO AND A HALF
MILLION DOLLAR DIAMOND

19:50.972 --> 19:52.147
IS A LOT BIGGER THAN
THE CHARM BRACELET

19:52.278 --> 19:53.322
I GOT FROM MY GRANDMA.

19:55.194 --> 19:56.325
ALRIGHT, BEN.

19:58.588 --> 19:59.589
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

19:59.720 --> 20:01.461
-DON'T GET ANY
IDEAS, ALRIGHT?

20:01.591 --> 20:05.160
YOU'RE FREEZING, YOU NEED TO
GET WARM, AND I'M ALL I GOT.

20:06.248 --> 20:07.684
I'VE NEVER HAD A FIRST
DATE DIE ON ME BEFORE

20:07.815 --> 20:09.556
AND I'M NOT GONNA LET
IT HAPPEN NOW, ALRIGHT?

20:11.993 --> 20:14.343
-WELL, WHEN YOU
GOTTA GO YA...

20:19.174 --> 20:20.044
-MEN.

20:26.573 --> 20:28.749
-HI, IT'S GREAT
TO SEE YOU GUYS!

20:29.837 --> 20:31.795
I HAVE A WONDERFUL
HAND TODAY.

20:32.753 --> 20:34.711
-I'M FEELING VERY LUCKY
TODAY, HOW YA DOIN'?

20:34.842 --> 20:36.583
-OKAY, WHOSE TURN IS IT?

20:36.713 --> 20:39.150
-[WOMEN TALKING]

20:41.675 --> 20:43.111
-HI, HOW WE DOIN'?

20:44.591 --> 20:47.594
NOW, FRANCIS, HAVE
FUN, BUT BE CAREFUL.

20:47.724 --> 20:50.118
OKAY, REMEMBER, BE CAREFUL.

20:53.382 --> 20:57.560
-[WOMEN TALKING]

21:09.442 --> 21:10.399
-[LAUGHS]

21:11.052 --> 21:11.922
HI!

21:15.012 --> 21:16.579
IT'S STILL MY TURN.

21:16.710 --> 21:21.280
-[WOMEN TALKING]

21:21.410 --> 21:23.630
-GRAND SLAM, WOO!

21:24.413 --> 21:26.415
THERE'S A RIGHT WAY
AND A WRONG WAY,

21:26.546 --> 21:27.721
AND A CON WAY!

21:27.851 --> 21:28.722
WOO!

21:28.852 --> 21:30.114
[LAUGHS]

21:36.382 --> 21:39.298
HEY, KIDS, NOT
TOO FAR OUT!

21:39.907 --> 21:40.777
-WOMAN: THEY'LL BE OKAY.

21:41.822 --> 21:43.998
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU THOUGHT
YOU WERE GOING TO DOUBLE ME.

21:44.128 --> 21:44.912
I'VE GOT A GREAT HAND!

21:45.042 --> 21:48.002
-[WOMEN TALKING]

21:55.879 --> 21:56.750
-CHILDREN: HELP!

21:59.100 --> 22:02.016
-OH MY GOSH, WE'VE
GOTTA GET OUT THERE!

22:02.146 --> 22:05.976
-[WOMEN TALKING EXCITEDLY]

22:14.202 --> 22:16.030
-WOMAN: CALL THE LIFEGUARD!

22:20.817 --> 22:23.167
-[WOMEN TALKING]

22:25.779 --> 22:29.870
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

23:22.226 --> 23:25.099
-WOMAN: OH MY GOSH,
THEY GAVE ME SUCH A SCARE!

23:26.317 --> 23:27.797
-OKAY, LADIES, CALM
DOWN CALM DOWN.

23:27.928 --> 23:29.364
WATCH YOUR STEP,
WATCH YOUR STEP.

23:31.497 --> 23:34.630
-[WOMEN TALKING]

23:36.415 --> 23:37.546
IS EVERYONE OKAY?

23:38.417 --> 23:39.461
IS EVERYBODY FINE HERE?

23:45.989 --> 23:46.947
GOOD JOB.

23:54.868 --> 23:55.825
-FRANCIS!

23:55.956 --> 23:57.479
WAS THIS A JOKE?

23:58.654 --> 24:00.961
WELL IT WASN'T THE
LEAST BIT FUNNY OR CUTE.

24:01.657 --> 24:04.225
AND I THINK YOU KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.

24:08.098 --> 24:08.969
-GOOD WORK, HOBIE.

24:10.449 --> 24:13.669
SO ARE YOU MOVIN'
OUT OR WHAT?

24:14.670 --> 24:16.324
-YEAH, IT'S A
PROBABLY A GOOD IDEA.

24:17.543 --> 24:19.066
COME ON, IT'S A
GREAT IDEA, RIGHT?

24:19.196 --> 24:20.763
-AREN'T YOU GONNA
ASK YOUR DAD FIRST?

24:22.112 --> 24:23.200
-I'M GONNA TELL HIM.

24:33.167 --> 24:34.168
-HOW MUCH LONGER?

24:35.169 --> 24:37.737
-HIGH TIDE'S
SCHEDULED FOR 3:35.

24:39.086 --> 24:40.740
THAT'S 20 MINUTES.

24:42.393 --> 24:44.178
-I'M GETTING REAL
TIRED OF WAITING.

24:52.403 --> 24:54.449
-OKAY, BEN YOU GOTTA
STAY AWAKE, YOU HEAR ME?

24:55.102 --> 24:57.583
WE'VE LOST A LOT OF BLOOD
AND YOU'RE GOIN' INTO SHOCK.

24:57.713 --> 24:59.715
YOU HAVE GOT
TO STAY AWAKE.

24:59.846 --> 25:01.500
COME ON TALK TO ME, BEN.

25:01.630 --> 25:02.718
COME ON.

25:02.849 --> 25:04.241
YEAH TALK TO ME, BUDDY.

25:04.372 --> 25:05.547
COME ON.

25:05.678 --> 25:06.505
TELL ME SOMETHIN'
ABOUT YOURSELF.

25:08.376 --> 25:10.465
NOW WE HAVE A PRETTY GOOD
CHANCE OF DYIN' HERE TOGETHER

25:10.596 --> 25:12.511
AND I DON'T KNOW THE
FIRST THING ABOUT YOU.

25:13.207 --> 25:14.643
TELL ME WHERE YOU
WERE BORN, ALRIGHT?

25:15.470 --> 25:16.515
-ALRIGHT, I...

25:18.212 --> 25:20.040
-TELL ME WHAT HIGH
SCHOOL YOU WENT TO?

25:20.170 --> 25:21.171
HUH?

25:21.302 --> 25:22.216
WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE MOVIE?

25:23.522 --> 25:24.871
-I'M REALLY SLEEPY...

25:25.001 --> 25:26.960
-NO, COME ON YOU CANNOT
GO TO SLEEP, BEN.

25:27.090 --> 25:28.048
COME ON WAKE UP!

25:28.178 --> 25:29.876
WAKE UP!

25:30.006 --> 25:32.052
YOU DON'T WANNA TALK, ALRIGHT
I'LL TALK, I'LL TALK.

25:32.182 --> 25:33.488
OKAY.

25:33.619 --> 25:35.534
I WAS BORN IN ST.
LOUIS, MISSOURI.

25:35.664 --> 25:39.668
MY FAMILY ALWAYS
SAID MISSOURABI, THEY
NEVER SAID MISSOURI.

25:39.799 --> 25:41.017
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY, IT WAS

25:41.148 --> 25:43.150
SOME KIND OF
FAMILY DYSFUNCTION.

25:45.065 --> 25:46.414
ARE YOU LISTENIN'
TO ME, BEN?

25:46.545 --> 25:47.328
COME ON.

25:47.458 --> 25:48.329
COME ON.

25:48.938 --> 25:50.461
COME ON, STAY AWAKE.

25:50.592 --> 25:52.115
COME ON, BEN.

25:54.378 --> 25:57.077
DID YOU KNOW THAT I HAVE
A PHOTOGRAPHIC MEMORY?

25:57.207 --> 25:58.121
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

25:58.252 --> 26:00.036
YEAH.

26:00.167 --> 26:02.256
I CAN LOOK AT SOMETHIN' ONCE
AND I CAN REMEMBER IT FOREVER.

26:03.779 --> 26:05.564
THE KIDS IN SCHOOL
THEY USED TO SAY

26:06.173 --> 26:09.176
THAT I WAS A KNOW IT
ALL BECAUSE I ALWAYS GOT

26:09.306 --> 26:11.961
100% ON MY TESTS AND I
DON'T KNOW WHY BECAUSE

26:12.788 --> 26:14.747
I JUST ALWAYS REMEMBERED
EVERYTHING, YOU KNOW?

26:15.269 --> 26:17.184
COME ON, BEN, ARE
YOU LISTENIN' TO ME?

26:17.314 --> 26:18.968
HUH?
COME ON, BUDDY.

26:19.099 --> 26:21.275
COME ON, STAY AWAKE!

26:26.410 --> 26:28.717
-[INSTRUMENTAL NEW AGE MUSIC]

26:30.545 --> 26:33.287
-♪ THE SEA IT FEELS COLD

26:34.201 --> 26:37.421
♪ HAS IT COME HERE TO RISE?

26:38.771 --> 26:41.338
♪ I CAN HEAR YOU BREATHE

26:42.165 --> 26:44.907
♪ AS IT KEEPS ME ALIVE

26:46.561 --> 26:49.390
♪ THIS LIFE AS IT DRAINS

26:49.520 --> 26:52.611
♪ SO SLOWLY TO THE SAND

26:54.264 --> 26:56.702
♪ OF A FOREIGN PAIN

26:57.528 --> 27:01.271
♪ OF ANOTHER KIND OF LOVE

27:06.494 --> 27:09.192
♪ THE GRACE OF YOUR HAND

27:18.549 --> 27:22.162
♪ I FEEL A MOMENTS GRACE

27:26.601 --> 27:31.519
♪ I FEEL A MOMENTS GRACE BY YOUR HAND

27:38.439 --> 27:41.268
♪ THE GRACE OF YOUR HANDS

27:50.451 --> 27:53.062
♪ THE LIGHT IT FADES

27:53.759 --> 27:57.110
♪ INTO THE SAND

27:58.633 --> 28:01.157
♪ THE VOICE JUST ECHOES

28:01.288 --> 28:07.250
♪ BEYOND THIS HOPELESS STAN

28:15.084 --> 28:16.564
-WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

28:16.695 --> 28:18.305
-THIS COMES UNDER THE
CATEGORY OF SHOWERING.

28:18.435 --> 28:20.524
-YOU KNOW DAMN WELL
WHAT I'M TALKIN' ABOUT.

28:20.655 --> 28:21.917
-I IMAGINE YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT HOBIE.

28:22.048 --> 28:24.093
-NEELY, HE CAN'T
LIVE WITH YOU.

28:24.224 --> 28:26.095
-HE CAN AND DOES, IT'S A
GOOD DEAL FOR BOTH OF US.

28:26.226 --> 28:28.707
-WHAT IS THIS, SOME SORT
OF WEIRD SORT OF PAYBACK?

28:28.837 --> 28:30.839
YOU CAN'T HURT ME, SO YOU
HURT ME THROUGH MY SON?

28:30.970 --> 28:32.362
-ARE YOU HURT?

28:32.493 --> 28:34.190
I'M SO SORRY, AND HERE I
THOUGHT WE WERE FRIENDS.

28:34.321 --> 28:36.062
-YOU CAN SHOVE THAT.

28:36.192 --> 28:38.151
YOU'RE JUST TRYIN' TO PRY ME
AND HOBIE APART AREN'T YOU?

28:38.891 --> 28:40.501
-HE'S NOT A CHILD, MITCH.

28:40.631 --> 28:41.763
AND I'M SORRY TO TELL YOU
THIS BUT HE DOESN'T NEED

28:41.894 --> 28:43.809
HIS DADDY TO DOTE
ON HIM ANYMORE.

28:43.939 --> 28:45.636
GUESS HE JUST LIKES BEING
WITH ME BETTER THEN.

28:46.507 --> 28:49.075
THERE I GO AGAIN,
SORRY, MITCH.

28:50.598 --> 28:54.994
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

28:56.691 --> 28:58.171
-YOU'RE ENJOYING
THIS, AREN'T YA?

29:14.578 --> 29:15.449
ALRIGHT.

29:16.276 --> 29:17.407
I'VE BEEN THINKIN'
ABOUT THIS.

29:18.321 --> 29:19.888
AND THIS IS NOT RIGHT,
YOU'RE NOT LIVIN' WITH NEELY.

29:20.019 --> 29:21.977
-DAD WE'VE ALREADY HAD
THIS CONVERSATION BEFORE!

29:22.108 --> 29:23.587
-YEAH, WELL WE'RE
NOT DONE YET.

29:23.718 --> 29:24.371
-YEAH, WE'RE NOT
GONNA BE DONE UNTIL

29:24.501 --> 29:25.459
YOU GET YOUR WAY, RIGHT?

29:25.589 --> 29:26.460
-ALRIGHT, ALRIGHT, LOOK.

29:27.330 --> 29:28.201
HOBIE.

29:28.941 --> 29:29.768
YOU'RE MY SON.

29:30.638 --> 29:31.682
I'M YOUR FATHER.

29:31.813 --> 29:33.554
YOU CANNOT LIVE
WITH MY EX-WIFE.

29:33.684 --> 29:35.512
-I'M OKAY WITH IT,
NEELY'S OKAY WITH IT,

29:35.643 --> 29:36.818
IT'S ONLY YOU.

29:37.514 --> 29:40.126
DAD I KNOW FEELINGS CHANGE
WHEN PEOPLE SPLIT UP.

29:40.648 --> 29:42.128
I REMEMBER WHEN YOU
AND MOM WERE TOGETHER.

29:42.258 --> 29:43.607
-NO, YOUR MOM AND
I WERE DIFFERENT.

29:43.738 --> 29:45.087
WE'RE FRIENDS.

29:45.218 --> 29:46.393
-YEAH, BUT IT
TAKES A WHILE.

29:46.523 --> 29:47.742
REMEMBER?

29:48.264 --> 29:49.178
MAYBE YOU AND NEELY--

29:49.309 --> 29:50.614
-NO, NO.

29:50.745 --> 29:52.529
NEELY AND I WILL
NEVER BE FRIENDS.

29:52.660 --> 29:53.748
-WELL YOU MARRIED
HER, YOU MUST HAVE

29:53.879 --> 29:55.184
SOME FEELINGS TOWARDS HER.

29:55.315 --> 29:56.098
-I KNOW, I KNOW.

29:56.229 --> 29:57.012
I WAS WRONG.

29:57.143 --> 29:58.144
I MADE A MISTAKE.

29:59.232 --> 30:00.276
-YEAH, WELL I
REALLY LIKE HER.

30:02.191 --> 30:03.018
-HOBIE.

30:03.540 --> 30:04.498
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW HER.

30:05.586 --> 30:06.848
-WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

30:06.979 --> 30:08.589
-WELL, SHE DOES THINGS,
SHE SAYS THINGS,

30:08.719 --> 30:10.460
AND SHE MEANS SOMETHING ELSE.

30:10.591 --> 30:12.245
-LOOK, I'M SORRY YOU
HAD A PROBLEM WITH HER

30:12.375 --> 30:14.116
BUT IT'S YOUR'S, NOT MINE.

30:14.682 --> 30:16.466
AND I DON'T THINK IT'S VERY
FAIR OF YOU TO TRASH HER.

30:16.597 --> 30:19.121
-I'M NOT TRASHING HER,
I'M JUST WARNING YOU.

30:19.818 --> 30:21.167
-YOU MAKE IT SOUND
LIKE SHE'S GOT SOME

30:21.297 --> 30:23.473
SPLIT PERSONALITY THING
GOING OR SOMETHIN'.

30:23.604 --> 30:24.474
-MAYBE SHE DOES.

30:24.605 --> 30:26.041
-YOU TOLD ME NOT
TO JUDGE PEOPLE

30:26.172 --> 30:27.695
BY WHAT OTHER PEOPLE
SAY ABOUT 'EM.

30:27.826 --> 30:29.305
-I'M NOT TALKIN'
ABOUT OTHER PEOPLE.

30:29.436 --> 30:30.916
I'M YOUR DAD.

30:31.046 --> 30:32.395
I'M JUST TRYING TO DO
WHAT'S BEST FOR YOU.

30:32.526 --> 30:33.962
-WELL, IT'S MY JOB TO DO
WHAT'S BEST FOR ME NOW.

30:34.093 --> 30:35.746
AND SHE HASN'T DONE
ANYTHING WRONG TO ME.

30:35.877 --> 30:37.139
-SHE'S DOIN' IT RIGHT NOW.

30:38.358 --> 30:39.185
SHE'S USIN' YOU.

30:39.315 --> 30:40.490
-NO, SHE'S HELPING ME.

30:40.621 --> 30:42.101
AND I SEE HER AS A FRIEND.

30:43.319 --> 30:45.147
DAD, WHEN YOU
AND MOM BROKE UP,

30:45.278 --> 30:47.367
YOU NEVER MADE ME CHOOSE
BETWEEN ONE OR THE OTHER.

30:47.497 --> 30:49.412
ME AND YOU HAD OUR
OWN RELATIONSHIP,

30:49.543 --> 30:51.545
AND ME AND MOM HAD
OUR OWN DEAL GOIN' ON.

30:51.675 --> 30:52.981
AND I LIKE THAT.

30:53.112 --> 30:54.678
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M
TRYIN' TO SAY HERE?

30:54.809 --> 30:55.723
-NO.

30:55.854 --> 30:56.811
I DON'T.

31:03.252 --> 31:05.733
-WE'RE GONNA HAVE SOME REAL
SERIOUS PROBLEMS TO DEAL WITH.

31:08.301 --> 31:12.348
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

31:22.837 --> 31:25.057
-ALRIGHT, WE'VE
GOT TWO CHOICES.

31:25.187 --> 31:26.754
WE EITHER STAY IN HERE
AND YOU BLEED TO DEATH

31:26.885 --> 31:28.625
OR WE STAY IN HERE AND
DIE, DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

31:28.756 --> 31:30.323
-BUT THEY'RE
STILL OUT THERE.

31:30.453 --> 31:32.020
-THIS CAVE IS GONNA FILL
UP WITH WATER ANY MINUTE,

31:32.151 --> 31:33.065
WE HAVE GOT TO
GET OUT OF HERE.

31:33.195 --> 31:34.109
LOOK AT ME.

31:34.240 --> 31:35.502
YOU ARE GOING TO DO THIS.

31:35.632 --> 31:36.807
-OKAY, OKAY.

31:36.938 --> 31:38.331
WHAT'S THE PLAN?

31:38.461 --> 31:39.767
-I'M GONNA BE MAKIN'
THAT UP AS WE GO ALONG.

31:39.898 --> 31:42.422
ALL YOU NEED IS A
REALLY BIG BREATH.

31:42.552 --> 31:43.336
YOU READY?

31:43.466 --> 31:44.685
-READY!
-OKAY.

31:50.038 --> 31:51.910
-TIDE ISN'T GETTING
ANY HIGHER THAN THIS.

31:52.736 --> 31:54.695
AND I'LL BE YA TWO MILLION
BUCKS MARCUS IS WONDERING

31:54.825 --> 31:56.262
WHY HIS DELIVERY
DIDN'T SHOW UP.

31:57.828 --> 31:59.439
JASON, WE NEED TO
GET OUT OF HERE.

32:01.702 --> 32:02.877
ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?!

32:03.008 --> 32:05.271
-I'M VERY AWARE
OF OUR SITUATION.

32:07.229 --> 32:10.580
NOW KEEP YOUR MOUTH SHUT
OR I'LL HANDLE THIS ALONE.

32:11.581 --> 32:12.582
UNDERSTAND?

32:14.889 --> 32:15.846
-I UNDERSTAND.

32:28.424 --> 32:33.429
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

33:05.722 --> 33:06.506
-DID YOU HEAR THAT?

33:06.636 --> 33:07.507
-YEAH.

33:08.551 --> 33:09.378
TURN ON THE FISH FINDER.

33:09.509 --> 33:12.903
-[GUNSHOTS]

33:13.469 --> 33:14.253
-COME ON!

33:14.383 --> 33:15.558
-IT WON'T COME ON!

33:18.213 --> 33:19.693
-LET'S FINISH THIS.

33:22.130 --> 33:25.481
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

33:37.015 --> 33:37.885
-OKAY.

33:41.149 --> 33:42.020
OKAY.

33:43.456 --> 33:44.326
-GO GO.

33:58.297 --> 33:59.559
-DIDN'T YOU
RECONNECT THE GAS?

33:59.689 --> 34:00.560
-YES!

34:02.431 --> 34:03.693
ALEX, LOOK OUT!

34:07.915 --> 34:08.697
-YOU OKAY?

34:08.829 --> 34:09.699
-LET'S GO!

34:10.351 --> 34:14.007
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

34:34.681 --> 34:35.985
CAN WE GET OUT OF HERE?

34:36.117 --> 34:37.335
PLEASE?

34:52.742 --> 34:54.309
-[WOMAN YELLS]

35:06.626 --> 35:08.845
-I'LL CALL IT INTO HARBOR
PATROL, THEY'LL PICK THEM UP.

35:10.412 --> 35:11.979
-NO RADIO.

35:12.110 --> 35:13.111
PUT IT DOWN.

35:16.462 --> 35:17.463
STOP THE BOAT.

35:17.985 --> 35:18.942
-OKAY, ALRIGHT.

35:21.945 --> 35:23.817
-HANDS ON THE
WHEEL, PLEASE.

35:27.560 --> 35:28.387
[BEN LAUGHS]

35:28.517 --> 35:29.562
-THOSE YOUR DIAMONDS?

35:30.780 --> 35:32.260
-NOW DON'T POUT.

35:33.043 --> 35:34.567
[BEN LAUGHS]

35:35.263 --> 35:38.701
YA KNOW, YOU REALLY BEEN
A BIG HELP TO ME, DARLIN'.

35:40.486 --> 35:42.792
-YOU KNOW I CAN USUALLY
JUDGE PEOPLE PRETTY WELL.

35:42.923 --> 35:44.838
I GOTTA ADMIT YOU'RE GOOD.

35:44.968 --> 35:46.405
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

35:47.710 --> 35:48.972
I'M BETTER.

35:49.103 --> 35:53.107
-[BOAT ENGINE REVS]

35:53.238 --> 35:57.198
-[INTENSE MUSIC]

36:18.872 --> 36:22.005
THIS IS A BAYWATCH LIFEGUARD
IN AN UNIDENTIFIED SCARAB.

36:22.136 --> 36:25.270
DRUG INTERVENTION 500
YARDS OFF PARADISE COVE.

36:25.400 --> 36:27.272
PEOPLE IN THE WATER
ARMED AND DANGEROUS,

36:27.402 --> 36:28.621
PLEASE RESPOND.

36:39.109 --> 36:39.980
-HEY.

36:42.287 --> 36:44.985
I JUST CAME BY TO GET
THE REST OF MY STUFF.

36:46.900 --> 36:47.944
-COME HERE FOR A SECOND.

36:48.684 --> 36:49.511
SIT DOWN.

36:50.208 --> 36:51.078
-YEAH.

36:57.345 --> 37:00.392
-LOOK, I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT THIS WHOLE THING AND,

37:01.697 --> 37:04.178
WELL, MAYBE WE BOTH SAID
SOME THINGS WE DIDN'T MEAN.

37:04.874 --> 37:05.745
-NO.

37:06.267 --> 37:07.964
EVERYTHING I SAID I MEANT.

37:08.704 --> 37:09.923
IT'S NO BIGGIE, RIGHT?

37:10.053 --> 37:12.012
-NO IT IS BIG, IT'S HUGE.

37:12.882 --> 37:13.927
HOBIE.

37:14.057 --> 37:14.928
I'M YOUR DAD.

37:16.146 --> 37:17.235
YOU'RE MY SON.

37:17.365 --> 37:18.279
WE'RE A TEAM.

37:19.715 --> 37:22.065
-I KNOW, WE'RE ALWAYS
GONNA BE A TEAM.

37:22.762 --> 37:24.633
BEING A TEAM DOESN'T MEAN
YOU HAVE TO LIVE TOGETHER

37:24.764 --> 37:25.591
THOUGH, DOES IT?

37:28.158 --> 37:29.943
-NO, NO, I GUESS NOT.

37:31.771 --> 37:33.251
-DID YOU REALLY THINK
I WAS GONNA LIVE HERE

37:33.381 --> 37:34.469
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE?

37:34.600 --> 37:36.732
-NO, JUST THE NEXT 25 YEARS.

37:36.863 --> 37:37.733
[LAUGHS]

37:38.821 --> 37:40.301
-WHENEVER I'M
HAVING A PROBLEM,

37:41.215 --> 37:44.262
YOU SAY TO ME, "WHAT
ARE YOU THINKING?

37:44.914 --> 37:45.828
HOW DO YOU FEEL?"

37:45.959 --> 37:47.830
SO NOW HOW DO YOU FEEL

37:47.961 --> 37:49.267
AND WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

37:50.572 --> 37:52.618
-YOU MEAN WHAT GOES
AROUND COMES AROUND?

37:55.142 --> 37:56.012
OKAY.

37:59.015 --> 37:59.886
HOBIE.

38:01.975 --> 38:05.065
I'M THINKIN' THAT WE'VE BEEN
TOGETHER EVERY SINGLE DAY

38:06.109 --> 38:07.415
SINCE THE DAY
YOU WERE BORN.

38:09.852 --> 38:13.465
AND I'M THINKIN' THAT
I REALLY LIKE THAT.

38:15.728 --> 38:17.904
AND I'M THINKING
THAT IF YOU MOVE OUT

38:20.559 --> 38:22.256
I MAY NEVER FEEL
THIS WAY AGAIN.

38:22.865 --> 38:24.867
-SO YOU REALLY WANNA
BE TELLIN' ME TO

38:24.998 --> 38:26.565
CLEAN MY ROOM WHEN I'M 90?

38:26.695 --> 38:28.175
-AT LEAST UNTIL YOU RETIRE.

38:28.306 --> 38:30.438
-[BOTH LAUGH]

38:30.569 --> 38:32.397
-I KNOW IT'S
SELFISH. I JUST...

38:34.268 --> 38:35.487
THAT'S WHAT I'M THINKING.

38:38.968 --> 38:40.405
I LOVE YA, HOBIE.

38:41.014 --> 38:42.711
-I KNOW, I LOVE YOU TOO.

38:44.757 --> 38:47.455
BUT IF ALL THIS
DOESN'T WORK OUT

38:47.586 --> 38:49.501
I CAN ALWAYS COME
BACK HERE, RIGHT?

38:50.284 --> 38:51.677
-OH I FORGOT TO TELL YOU.

38:52.373 --> 38:53.853
I'VE ALREADY RENTED
YOUR ROOM OUT.

38:55.985 --> 38:58.423
-[BOTH LAUGH]

39:02.035 --> 39:03.036
-COME ON.

39:03.166 --> 39:03.950
I'LL HELP YOU PACK.

39:04.080 --> 39:04.951
-ALRIGHT.

39:06.561 --> 39:08.041
-MITCH: TAKE OUT THE
TRASH ONE MORE TIME?

39:08.171 --> 39:09.521
-HOBIE: YEAH, I THINK
I COULD HANDLE THAT.

39:11.479 --> 39:15.527
-[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING]

39:23.404 --> 39:24.492
-HEY, GRA--!

39:30.455 --> 39:31.673
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, GRANDMA.

39:34.502 --> 39:35.982
[SIGHS]

39:36.678 --> 39:37.897
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

39:44.164 --> 39:45.121
-HEY.
-HEY!

39:45.818 --> 39:47.515
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

39:47.646 --> 39:48.995
-WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH,
BUT IT'S NOT MY BIRTHDAY.

39:49.125 --> 39:50.431
-I KNOW THAT, IT'S
MY GRANNY'S BUT SHE'S

39:50.562 --> 39:52.085
IN VEGAS WITH ED.

39:52.215 --> 39:54.870
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME WINE
BECAUSE I CERTAINLY WOULD.

39:57.133 --> 39:58.178
-HEARD YOU HAD AN
INTERESTING DAY.

39:58.308 --> 39:59.135
-OH YEAH.

39:59.266 --> 40:00.006
-AH, IT'S OVER THERE.

40:00.136 --> 40:01.050
WHAT HAPPENED?

40:01.181 --> 40:02.574
-WELL, LET'S SEE.

40:02.704 --> 40:04.445
I JUMPED OFF A CLIFF.

40:04.576 --> 40:05.925
I GOT SHOT AT.

40:06.055 --> 40:07.883
AND THEN I PUNCHED
ON A WOMAN.

40:08.014 --> 40:09.145
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

40:09.276 --> 40:10.190
-AH...

40:10.973 --> 40:12.410
-WHAT?

40:12.540 --> 40:14.977
-ALEX, HOW OLD WERE
YOU WHEN LEFT HOME?

40:15.108 --> 40:16.326
-LET'S SEE, WHICH TIME?

40:17.153 --> 40:19.721
I LEFT HOME EVERY OTHER
WEEK SINCE I WAS EIGHT.

40:19.852 --> 40:21.984
AND I NEVER STAYED GONE
LONGER THAN AN HOUR.

40:22.115 --> 40:22.898
-NO, THE LAST TIME.

40:23.029 --> 40:23.812
THE FINAL TIME.

40:23.943 --> 40:24.770
-FINAL TIME?

40:24.900 --> 40:27.207
I WAS 18 AND CHANGE.

40:29.383 --> 40:30.732
-HOW'D YOUR PARENTS
FEEL ABOUT THAT?

40:31.646 --> 40:33.474
-WELL, I HAVE GOT SIX
BROTHERS AND SISTERS

40:33.605 --> 40:36.216
SO THEY DIDN'T EVEN NOTICE
I WAS GONE UNTIL I WAS 25.

40:40.960 --> 40:42.178
YOU'RE SERIOUS, AREN'T YOU?

40:42.309 --> 40:44.398
-HOBIE MOVED OUT TODAY.

40:44.529 --> 40:45.399
-MM.

40:46.792 --> 40:48.141
SO YOU FEELIN'
A LITTLE BLUE?

40:48.271 --> 40:49.969
-NO, I'M FEELING A
LOT LOST, YOU KNOW.

40:50.099 --> 40:51.579
BEING A DAD IS
A FULL TIME JOB.

40:51.710 --> 40:54.452
I JUST DON'T KNOW WHAT
TO DO WITH MYSELF.

40:55.757 --> 40:57.759
-LISTEN, YOU HAVE DONE
A GREAT JOB WITH HOBIE

40:57.890 --> 41:00.327
BUT I'VE GOT NEWS FOR
YA IT'S NOT OVER YET.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.547
HE'S JUST OUT THERE GETTING
ON THE JOB TRAINING.

41:02.677 --> 41:03.983
IT'S A NATURAL PROCESS.

41:04.113 --> 41:05.245
-YEAH, WELL IT SUCKS.

41:05.375 --> 41:06.202
-ALEX: HE'LL BE BACK.

41:06.333 --> 41:07.639
-HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

41:07.769 --> 41:08.727
-[DOOR OPENS]

41:09.379 --> 41:10.163
-HEY, DAD.

41:10.293 --> 41:11.077
-MITCH: HEY.

41:11.207 --> 41:12.208
-HEY, ALEX.

41:12.339 --> 41:13.166
-WELL, HELLO, PRODIGAL SON.

41:14.689 --> 41:15.864
-CAN I BORROW TWENTY BUCKS?

41:17.649 --> 41:19.215
-YEAH, SURE.

41:19.346 --> 41:20.173
-I'LL PAY YOU BACK
ON PAYDAY, THANKS.

41:20.869 --> 41:21.740
-HERE YA GO.

41:21.870 --> 41:22.784
-BYE.

41:22.915 --> 41:23.698
BYE, ALEX!

41:23.829 --> 41:24.656
-SEE YA.

41:27.528 --> 41:30.096
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE YOUR JOB
MIGHT BE SAFE AFTER ALL, DAD.

41:32.577 --> 41:33.360
-CHEERS.

41:33.491 --> 41:34.404
-CHEERS.

41:34.535 --> 41:39.409
-[UPBEAT ELECTRONIC MUSIC]

41:45.198 --> 41:49.245
-[END THEME PLAYING]
